Bothriocephalus acheilognathi
is distributed throughout Africa, but its abundance is considerably lower than in newly colonized regions, especially in Europe and North America (
García-Prieto & Osorio-Sarabia 1991
;
Williams & Jones 1994
;
Salgado-Maldonado & Pineda-López 2003
). The absence of records from West Africa is probably artificial, because great majority of parasitological studies on cyprinids in this region were obviously focused solely on ectoparasitic monogeneans (see
Khalil & Polling 1997
).
